I don't really want to be an MLB player!

768
00:53:07,017 --> 00:53:10,437
Even if I go to the States,
I won't even be that happy!

769
00:53:10,896 --> 00:53:12,147
Then why did you lie to me?

770
00:53:12,230 --> 00:53:14,191
Why did you say you'll become
an MLB player?

771
00:53:14,274 --> 00:53:15,859
What about you? Why did you lie?

772
00:53:15,942 --> 00:53:17,277
When did I lie?

773
00:53:17,360 --> 00:53:19,279
You told me that I'm all you need!

774
00:53:23,241 --> 00:53:25,368
What kind of a mom gets married?

775
00:53:28,622 --> 00:53:30,874
None of the other kids' moms get married!

776
00:53:33,668 --> 00:53:37,380
Do you even know how it feels
to watch your own mom get married?

777
00:53:41,635 --> 00:53:43,970
At least you get to marry
since you're an adult!

778
00:53:46,431 --> 00:53:48,725
But I can't do that
because I'm a kid!

779
00:53:49,851 --> 00:53:51,853
It's not like
I can go to the army, either!

780
00:53:53,355 --> 00:53:55,440
I have nowhere to go!

781
00:54:00,153 --> 00:54:01,696
This is so annoying!

782
00:54:02,656 --> 00:54:05,033
Life is so annoying!

783
00:54:08,245 --> 00:54:09,412
So hurry up and choose!

784
00:54:09,496 --> 00:54:12,249
Are you going to come with me or not?

785
00:54:12,832 --> 00:54:14,709
I'll go with you.

786
00:54:27,806 --> 00:54:29,015
Dongbaek.

787
00:54:29,099 --> 00:54:31,017
Wait. Where are you going?

788
00:54:31,268 --> 00:54:32,769
How did you even come here?

789
00:54:46,032 --> 00:54:47,284
I told you, right?

790
00:54:47,367 --> 00:54:50,370
If they try to do something,
punch their nose. It's the nose.

791
00:54:57,335 --> 00:54:59,296
Did you just punch my nose?

792
00:55:02,299 --> 00:55:04,551
Did you know that Pil-gu eats

793
00:55:04,843 --> 00:55:06,928
instant rice and pickled radish for lunch?

794
00:55:07,929 --> 00:55:10,890
What?
I thought you applied for school lunch.

795
00:55:10,974 --> 00:55:14,269
You don't get to say anything
regarding Pil-gu from now on.

796
00:55:14,352 --> 00:55:15,437
You're out.

797
00:55:16,146 --> 00:55:19,024
Dongbaek, if you keep doing this,
it'll only confuse him.

798
00:55:20,483 --> 00:55:23,737
I don't need his uncle to worry about him.

799
00:55:24,863 --> 00:55:27,490
Are you his uncle?

800
00:55:28,158 --> 00:55:31,786
Were you worried he might get in trouble
if people found out he's your son?

801
00:55:31,870 --> 00:55:34,581
How do you think I feel?
I can't even say I'm his dad.

802
00:55:34,664 --> 00:55:36,207
Will you stop being emotional?

803
00:55:36,291 --> 00:55:38,752
I won't let my son stay
at his uncle's house

804
00:55:38,835 --> 00:55:41,880
and take instant rice and pickled radish
to school for lunch.

805
00:55:42,547 --> 00:55:45,592
This is my first time.
You need to let me adjust to all this.

806
00:55:46,176 --> 00:55:49,054
I'm not going to get swayed
by any of your bullshit anymore.

807
00:55:50,096 --> 00:55:51,639
Listen to me carefully.

808
00:55:51,723 --> 00:55:54,142
If you get involved in Pil-gu's life
one more time,

809
00:55:54,517 --> 00:55:57,604
I'll file a paternity suit
and make the whole world find out,

810
00:55:57,854 --> 00:55:59,606
so you'd better be prepared next time.

811
00:56:07,989 --> 00:56:09,407
Dongbaek!

812
00:56:10,700 --> 00:56:11,701
Pil-gu!

813
00:56:29,594 --> 00:56:32,680
I was the one
whom I needed to destroy, not Joker.

814
00:56:34,641 --> 00:56:37,894
Aren't you just sick and tired
of being intimidated all the time?

815
00:56:37,977 --> 00:56:41,106
People keep acting up
because I'm nice to them.

816
00:56:41,648 --> 00:56:44,901
I'm a person who's capable
of breaking someone's nose with my fist.

817
00:56:45,110 --> 00:56:47,821
And I'm a fighter
who's able to protect my own kid.

818
00:56:47,904 --> 00:56:50,407
Mom, you were like Conor McGregor.

819
00:56:51,658 --> 00:56:52,700
Really?

820
00:56:52,784 --> 00:56:56,454
I decided to become the strongest mother
in the world from now on.

821
00:57:00,041 --> 00:57:02,377
THE SERIAL KILLER JOKER
GETS ARRESTED IN SIX YEARS

822
00:57:02,460 --> 00:57:05,380
-What was your motive?
-Do you admit it?

823
00:57:05,463 --> 00:57:07,549
-Do you admit to the charges?
-Over here!

824
00:57:07,632 --> 00:57:09,175
-Wait!
-He said something!

825
00:57:09,259 --> 00:57:10,718
Wait a second! What did you say?

826
00:57:10,802 --> 00:57:13,138
-Can you say it a bit louder?
-You're so noisy!

827
00:57:16,516 --> 00:57:18,143
Why is killing someone a big deal?

828
00:57:19,561 --> 00:57:20,979
Stop causing a big fuss.

829
00:57:21,604 --> 00:57:24,190
-Let's go.
-What was your motive?

830
00:57:24,274 --> 00:57:25,900
-Please tell us!
-Why did you do it?

831
00:57:25,984 --> 00:57:27,610
-Look over here!
-Wait!

832
00:57:29,988 --> 00:57:31,364
Thank you.

833
00:57:35,243 --> 00:57:37,996
It's apparently
an antisocial personality disorder

834
00:57:38,121 --> 00:57:39,539
or something like that.

835
00:57:41,958 --> 00:57:44,752
Who cares what goes on
in the mind of that psycho?

836
00:57:45,086 --> 00:57:46,838
The most important thing

837
00:57:47,338 --> 00:57:50,425
is the fact that we, the nice guys,
did our best to catch that jerk.

838
00:57:50,925 --> 00:57:52,385
That's what this is all about.

839
00:57:53,052 --> 00:57:56,264
Are you coming from a wedding?

840
00:57:57,474 --> 00:58:00,560
You know, Parisians.
Even when there's a terrorist attack,

841
00:58:00,643 --> 00:58:03,813
they still go to a cafe the next day
and drink coffee.

842
00:58:04,063 --> 00:58:06,524
"There's absolutely nothing
you can take away from us."

843
00:58:06,608 --> 00:58:09,444
That's what they're trying to show
as they drink that coffee.

844
00:58:09,527 --> 00:58:10,820
Have you ever been to Paris?

845
00:58:16,034 --> 00:58:18,244
You wanted to do an interview, didn't you?

846
00:58:20,371 --> 00:58:24,209
I actually contributed
to this investigation, too.

847
00:58:25,210 --> 00:58:26,252
Yes, I know.

848
00:58:29,714 --> 00:58:32,091
Why isn't she picking up?

849
00:58:45,939 --> 00:58:50,985
YONG-SIK

850
00:59:09,212 --> 00:59:11,047
He's still such a baby.

851
00:59:15,134 --> 00:59:17,720
Pil-gu has protected me all his life.

852
00:59:17,804 --> 00:59:19,639
Mom, I caught a camel cricket!

853
00:59:19,847 --> 00:59:23,101
-Mom, look.
-My gosh, just throw it outside!

854
00:59:23,184 --> 00:59:25,228
-Look at it!
-Pil-gu, just throw it away!

855
00:59:25,311 --> 00:59:28,314
Mom, you can go to the bathroom now.
You can poop now!

856
00:59:29,649 --> 00:59:31,985
I'm sorry.

857
00:59:38,449 --> 00:59:40,827
Pil-gu saved me by coming to this world.

858
00:59:40,994 --> 00:59:43,538
And as he grew up,
he became a fighter to protect me.

859
00:59:43,621 --> 00:59:45,331
Why do I need to protect you?

860
00:59:45,915 --> 00:59:47,542
You should be protecting me.

861
00:59:48,042 --> 00:59:49,544
I was becoming a little girl.

862
00:59:50,253 --> 00:59:53,590
We won't be living together
once I grow old and get married, right?

863
00:59:53,673 --> 00:59:55,258
But he was becoming an adult.

864
00:59:55,341 --> 00:59:56,384
Isn't that how it is?

865
00:59:56,467 --> 00:59:57,510
Grandma!

866
00:59:58,970 --> 01:00:02,223
I didn't know that little kid was
just putting up with me.

867
01:00:03,224 --> 01:00:05,727
I betrayed him and was busy being in love.

868
01:00:08,771 --> 01:00:10,064
My gosh, Dongbaek!

869
01:00:10,148 --> 01:00:12,317
What took you so long
to answer your phone?

870
01:00:12,650 --> 01:00:14,485
My gosh, seriously.

871
01:00:15,236 --> 01:00:18,573
I'm sorry.
I couldn't answer the phone earlier.

872
01:00:18,656 --> 01:00:19,949
Did you see the news or not?

873
01:00:20,325 --> 01:00:22,160
Tell me! Hurry up!

874
01:00:22,952 --> 01:00:24,662
Thank you so much.

875
01:00:26,039 --> 01:00:28,333
I would've been scared all my life

876
01:00:28,958 --> 01:00:30,543
if it weren't for you.

877
01:00:31,753 --> 01:00:33,796
I'll head over to your bar right now.

878
01:00:33,880 --> 01:00:37,508
-So you'd better compliment me.
-No, don't come to the bar.

879
01:00:39,427 --> 01:00:42,472
I'll meet you at the place
where I first fell for you.

880
01:00:44,015 --> 01:00:44,849
What?

881
01:00:53,483 --> 01:00:54,317
Dongbaek!

882
01:01:01,366 --> 01:01:03,451
My gosh, why is he always
smiling like that?

883
01:01:03,951 --> 01:01:10,541
ONGSAN

884
01:01:18,675 --> 01:01:21,135
Is this where you fell for me?

885
01:01:23,888 --> 01:01:25,848
What was that kiss for?

886
01:01:27,100 --> 01:01:29,102
When I saw you sitting here,

887
01:01:29,268 --> 01:01:32,939
you have no idea how emotional I became.

888
01:01:34,857 --> 01:01:37,402
Back then, my heart fluttered like crazy

889
01:01:38,194 --> 01:01:40,947
just by sitting next to you.

890
01:01:41,948 --> 01:01:46,786
But now, we're close enough
to kiss each other.

891
01:01:47,537 --> 01:01:50,957
This is practically

892
01:01:51,040 --> 01:01:53,042
a miracle.

893
01:01:54,127 --> 01:01:57,922
Why would you kiss me like that?
Seriously. That was so unnecessary.

894
01:02:01,467 --> 01:02:02,677
What's the matter?

895
01:02:03,094 --> 01:02:04,762
Is it because I kissed you?

896
01:02:04,846 --> 01:02:08,683
My gosh, you used to kiss me first.
Why are you so shy all of a sudden?

897
01:02:09,767 --> 01:02:11,894
My gosh, how am I going to do this?

898
01:02:16,232 --> 01:02:18,526
What am I going to do?

899
01:02:20,027 --> 01:02:21,404
I can't say it.

900
01:02:21,988 --> 01:02:24,365
What? What's wrong?

901
01:02:24,449 --> 01:02:26,200
Did something happen again?

902
01:02:38,588 --> 01:02:39,922
My gosh, I can't...

903
01:02:40,006 --> 01:02:42,008
I didn't want to cry
when I say this to you.

904
01:02:46,929 --> 01:02:49,015
I'm so bad at saying goodbye.

905
01:03:00,526 --> 01:03:01,402
Yong-sik.

906
01:03:02,445 --> 01:03:05,323
What? Why are you looking at me like that?

907
01:03:06,199 --> 01:03:08,659
What kind of nonsense
are you going to say this time?

908
01:03:17,251 --> 01:03:20,838
My gosh, who dumps someone
and cries like a baby at the same time?

909
01:03:38,731 --> 01:03:41,275
I don't want to hurt Pil-gu
just so I can be happy.

910
01:03:42,276 --> 01:03:44,111
Does he hate me that much?

911
01:03:44,695 --> 01:03:46,280
Is he totally against me?

912
01:03:47,532 --> 01:03:49,492
I'd rather feel better if he said that.

913
01:03:49,659 --> 01:03:51,035
But he keeps...

914
01:03:51,911 --> 01:03:54,831
He keeps walking on eggshells.
He's starting to become like me.

915
01:04:00,253 --> 01:04:01,754
Dating was never an option.

916
01:04:03,172 --> 01:04:04,715
Pil-gu always comes first,

917
01:04:04,882 --> 01:04:07,885
but I was being so immature.

918
01:04:09,637 --> 01:04:10,721
It's okay.

919
01:04:11,472 --> 01:04:15,726
I'll try harder and win brownie points.
Don't worry.

920
01:04:15,810 --> 01:04:16,978
I thought...

921
01:04:18,563 --> 01:04:20,189
things would work that way.

922
01:04:23,693 --> 01:04:27,280
But that's just what we want.

923
01:04:42,253 --> 01:04:43,546
Ever since

924
01:04:44,297 --> 01:04:45,923
Pil-gu began talking,

925
01:04:47,216 --> 01:04:48,968
he told me that he'll protect me.

926
01:04:51,387 --> 01:04:53,514
And the fact that he thinks that way

927
01:04:53,598 --> 01:04:55,850
makes me feel so sorry and troubled.

928
01:05:03,774 --> 01:05:04,775
My gosh.

929
01:05:06,152 --> 01:05:07,695
Why do you have to be...

930
01:05:09,280 --> 01:05:10,740
so adamant?

931
01:05:12,074 --> 01:05:14,744
Pil-gu's still a little kid.

932
01:05:16,954 --> 01:05:18,247
What matters to me the most

933
01:05:18,873 --> 01:05:22,293
is to make sure Pil-gu grows up
to be a happy and confident kid.

934
01:05:29,342 --> 01:05:31,302
I thought timings and variables

935
01:05:31,802 --> 01:05:33,971
were all just a bunch of bullshit.

936
01:05:36,599 --> 01:05:39,435
I already knew what I needed to say

937
01:05:39,518 --> 01:05:41,520
to make this kind Hulk give up on me.

938
01:05:45,358 --> 01:05:46,484
I just want...

939
01:05:48,736 --> 01:05:50,112
to be a mom.

940
01:05:51,697 --> 01:05:53,741
I don't want to be just a woman.

941
01:05:55,910 --> 01:05:57,495
I want to be happy as a mom.

942
01:06:04,710 --> 01:06:05,878
My gosh.

943
01:06:09,590 --> 01:06:11,050
You're so mean.

944
01:06:14,804 --> 01:06:16,138
What am I supposed to say...

945
01:06:20,685 --> 01:06:22,311
to that?

946
01:06:23,479 --> 01:06:24,814
There's nothing you can do.

947
01:06:25,564 --> 01:06:26,899
We'll just have to break up.

948
01:06:32,071 --> 01:06:36,158
I didn't know how I was going to break up
with Dongbaek,

949
01:06:36,867 --> 01:06:38,995
but I didn't know
how to hold onto her, either.

950
01:07:06,981 --> 01:07:11,068
That's how my mom's
miraculous spring day came to an end.

951
01:07:13,904 --> 01:07:17,992
And with her love and affection,
I finally grew up.

952
01:07:18,075 --> 01:07:19,285
Yes, I ate.

953
01:07:19,368 --> 01:07:21,120
Why do you always ask if I ate or not?

954
01:07:22,705 --> 01:07:25,207
Yes, okay.
Mom, I'm a little busy right now.

955
01:07:25,291 --> 01:07:26,917
So stop calling me.

956
01:07:29,128 --> 01:07:30,713
Okay, I'll be right there.

957
01:08:07,792 --> 01:08:08,918
What do you mean?

958
01:08:11,212 --> 01:08:15,174
They're all edited. Those jealous brats
edited those photos!

959
01:08:16,217 --> 01:08:18,052
She was awfully lonely.

960
01:08:19,178 --> 01:08:21,222
Don't leave Dongbaek's side.

961
01:08:21,680 --> 01:08:23,349
I must live with you for 20 years.

962
01:08:23,432 --> 01:08:27,269
A death benefit won't make up
for all those years. So just live.

963
01:08:27,353 --> 01:08:29,522
If you miss this chance,
you won't make it.

964
01:08:29,605 --> 01:08:30,523
No, I won't do it.

